list of syscalls:
	1 - sys_exit - int(error code)
	2 - sys_fork - struct pt_regs
	3 - sys_read - uint(filedesc), char *(buffer), size_t(count)
	4 - sys_write - uint(filedesc), const char*(buffer), size_t(count)
	5 - sys_open - const char *(filename), int(flags), int(mode)
		flags: ???
		mode: ???
	6 - sys_close - unsigned int(fd)

	29 (0x1D) - sys_pause - no args

For filedesc, to read/write to stdin/stdout, use "1".

0x80 - syscall interrupt
format:
	eax - syscall # / return value
	ebx - param1
	ecx - param2
	edx - param3
	esi - param4
	edi - param5
	ebp - param6
syscall - dedicated instruction for this (apparently faster)
format:
	rax - syscall # / return value
	rdi - param1
	rsi - param2
	rdx - param3
	r10 - param4
	r8 - param5
	p9 - param6
